# OS
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db
desktop.ini

# Editor / IDE — ignore personal .vscode files, but COMMIT the two shared ones
# (recommended extensions + format-on-save) so the editor helps every contributor.
.vscode/*
!.vscode/extensions.json
!.vscode/settings.json
.idea/
*.swp
*~

# Agent / session state (never track) — but COMMIT the shared project settings
# (commit/PR attribution policy) so every lane's worktree inherits it.
**/.claude/*
!/.claude/settings.json

# Secrets / local config (KEEP OUT OF GIT)
.env
.env.*
# but DO commit the template (establishes the .env habit):
!.env.example
secrets.h
wifi_credentials.h

# Environmental context: the rig's HOME coordinates + the weather cache (PRD-0002 R6 /
# ADR-0013 §3) - the repo is public-ready, so these MUST NEVER be committed.
config/location.local.json
reports/weather/
# but DO commit the placeholder template:
!config/location.example.json
# Multi-device fleet registry (#485): board + per-channel plant assignments. The real
# fleet (home layout) stays local; the placeholder template IS committed.
config/devices.local.json
!config/devices.example.json
# Plant / pot / site profile registry (#675, ADR-0029): pot sizes + home placement
# describe the maintainer's windowsill; the real instance stays local, template committed.
config/plant_profiles.local.json
!config/plant_profiles.example.json
credentials.h
# identifier-guard denylist (#558): operator-sensitive literals the guard greps
# committed text for - home network names + hostnames, and any term to keep out of the
# public tree (e.g. unannounced companion-project codenames). Committing it would leak them.
config/identifiers.local.txt
# Pre-edit backups of the local configs (e.g. devices.local.json.bak-<ts>) - local safety copies.
config/*.local.json.bak*
# Manual watering journal (#1137 "glug glug"): the maintainer's real waterings are local
# operator ground truth, an append-only JSONL stream that grows per plant per season. Same
# local-operator-data class as the configs above - stays on the machine, never committed.
config/watering_log.local.jsonl
# Plant photos (#875 card identity block): camera photos carry EXIF/GPS of the
# maintainer's home - a hard privacy fence, same class as the home coordinates above. The
# real photos stay LOCAL; only a committed .gitkeep marks the dir. Exact path/format/size
# convention is a grill question; the never-commit fence is not.
config/photos/*
!config/photos/.gitkeep

# PlatformIO
.pio/
.pioenvs/
.piolibdeps/

# ESP-IDF component manager scaffold - auto-written by the arduino-esp32 framework the
# first time it builds on IDF5+ (pioarduino pin, #529); not authored, not portable across
# machines, safe to regenerate.
firmware/src/idf_component.yml
firmware/src/idf_component.yml.orig

# Arduino build artifacts
build/
*.bin
*.elf
*.hex
*.map

# Web-flasher: the manifest + image are copied next to the page for local testing (#271);
# they're per-build artifacts, never committed (*.bin already covers the image).
docs/flash/manifest.json

# Python (logging / analysis tooling, if added later)
__pycache__/
*.pyc
.venv/
venv/
# Tool caches — self-ignored by the tools too, but owned here so it doesn't
# depend on each tool's nested .gitignore.
.pytest_cache/
.ruff_cache/
.mypy_cache/

# Native (host) test build artifacts
tests/native/*.exe
tests/native/*.o

# Logs / scratch
*.log
logs/
_scratch/

# Experiment-mode raw captures (Epic 1) - isolated from logs/, never tracked.
# Root-anchored (/) so docs/experiments/ (notes + characterization plans) stays tracked - ADR-0017 §7.
/experiments/

# Generated analysis output (derived from logs/, rebuilt by tools/analytics - never tracked)
reports/

# Git LFS data-archive worktree (B8) - linked worktree on the `data` branch
.data-worktree/

# Local-only evidence video (kept out of git to avoid permanent repo bloat)
*.mov
*.MOV
.gstack/

# Retired flat backlog (migrated to GitHub Issues; carried a name leak) — untracked, kept on disk only
BACKLOG.md
